# Yulaa 2.0 — Workflow Smoke Tests
# VS Code REST Client format  (install "REST Client" extension by Huachao Mao)
#
# Usage:
#   1. Set the variables below to match your environment
#   2. Click "Send Request" above any ### block
#   3. Run tests top-to-bottom for a full end-to-end smoke pass
#
# Run order:
#   0. Seed defaults
#   1–3. Admission flow
#   4–6. Leave flow
#   7–8. Attendance regularization
#   9.   Generic workflow config check
#   10.  Leave balance check

@BASE_URL    = http://localhost:3000
@ADMIN_TOKEN = REPLACE_WITH_SCHOOL_ADMIN_JWT
@SUPER_TOKEN = REPLACE_WITH_SUPER_ADMIN_JWT
@TEACHER_TOKEN = REPLACE_WITH_TEACHER_JWT
@PRINCIPAL_TOKEN = REPLACE_WITH_PRINCIPAL_JWT
@PARENT_TOKEN  = REPLACE_WITH_PARENT_JWT
@SCHOOL_ID   = REPLACE_WITH_SCHOOL_UUID
@APP_ID      = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_1
@LEAVE_ID    = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_4
@REG_ID      = REPLACE_AFTER_STEP_7
@ATT_ID      = REPLACE_WITH_ATTENDANCE_RECORD_UUID

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 0 — Seed all default workflows (run once per school)
# Expected: { "ok": true, seeded: { admissionWorkflow: "created", ... } }
# Re-run is safe — all keys return "skipped" on second call
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 0a. Seed defaults (school admin)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admin/seed-workflows
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### 0b. Seed defaults (super admin targeting specific school)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admin/seed-workflows
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schoolId": "{{SCHOOL_ID}}"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — ADMISSION: Submit application (as parent)
# Expected: 201, { application: { id, status: "submitted", currentStep: 0 } }
# Copy returned application id → set @APP_ID above
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Submit admission application
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications
Authorization: Bearer {{PARENT_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schoolId":           "{{SCHOOL_ID}}",
  "parentName":         "Priya Sharma",
  "parentPhone":        "9876543210",
  "parentEmail":        "priya@example.com",
  "residentialAddress": "123 MG Road, Bengaluru",
  "children": [
    {
      "firstName":    "Riya",
      "lastName":     "Sharma",
      "dateOfBirth":  "2015-04-12",
      "gender":       "female",
      "classApplying": "5"
    }
  ]
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — ADMISSION: List pending applications (as admin)
# Expected: 200, { applications: [...] } — should include the one from Step 1
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2. List pending admission applications
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3a — ADMISSION: Approve Step 1 (Admin Review)
# Expected: 200, { application: { currentStep: 1, status: "step_approved" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3a. Approve admission Step 1 (Admin)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications/{{APP_ID}}/action
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":  "approve",
  "comment": "Documents verified"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3b — ADMISSION: Approve Step 2 (Principal Approval — isFinal)
# Expected: 200, { application: { status: "approved" } }
#           Student record auto-provisioned; fee invoice created
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3b. Approve admission Step 2 (Principal — final)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications/{{APP_ID}}/action
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":  "approve",
  "comment": "Admitted to Grade 5 - A"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3c — ADMISSION: Reject (alternative to approve)
# Expected: 200, { application: { status: "rejected" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3c. Reject admission application
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications/{{APP_ID}}/action
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":  "reject",
  "comment": "Documents incomplete"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — LEAVE: Submit leave request (as teacher)
# Expected: 201, { leave: { id, status: "pending" } }
# Copy returned leave id → set @LEAVE_ID above
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4. Submit leave request (teacher)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{TEACHER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "leave_type": "CL",
  "start_date": "2026-06-15",
  "end_date":   "2026-06-16",
  "reason":     "Personal work"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 5 — LEAVE: List leave requests (as principal)
# Expected: 200, { leaves: [...] } — should include the one from Step 4
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 5. List pending leave requests (principal view)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave?status=pending
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6a — LEAVE: Approve leave (as principal)
# Expected: 200, { leave: { status: "approved" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6a. Approve leave request
PATCH {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":  "approved",
  "id":      "{{LEAVE_ID}}",
  "comment": "Approved"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6b — LEAVE: Reject leave (alternative)
# Expected: 200, { leave: { status: "rejected" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6b. Reject leave request
PATCH {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":  "rejected",
  "id":      "{{LEAVE_ID}}",
  "comment": "School function on this date"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 6c — LEAVE: Withdraw (by submitter)
# Expected: 200, { leave: { status: "withdrawn" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 6c. Withdraw leave (teacher)
PATCH {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{TEACHER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "withdraw",
  "id":     "{{LEAVE_ID}}"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 7 — ATTENDANCE REGULARIZATION: Submit request (as teacher)
# Prereq: @ATT_ID must be a real Attendance record ID from your DB
# Expected: 201, { regularization: { id, status: "pending" } }
# Copy returned id → set @REG_ID above
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 7. Submit attendance regularization
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/attendance/regularization
Authorization: Bearer {{TEACHER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "attendanceId": "{{ATT_ID}}",
  "studentId":    "REPLACE_WITH_STUDENT_UUID",
  "toStatus":     "present",
  "reason":       "Student attended but was incorrectly marked absent due to system error"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 8a — ATTENDANCE REGULARIZATION: Approve (as principal)
# Expected: 200, { regularization: { status: "approved" } }
#           Attendance record updated to toStatus
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 8a. Approve regularization
PATCH {{BASE_URL}}/api/attendance/regularization?id={{REG_ID}}
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":        "approved",
  "reviewComment": "Verified with physical register"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 8b — ATTENDANCE REGULARIZATION: Reject (alternative)
# Expected: 200, { regularization: { status: "rejected" } }
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 8b. Reject regularization
PATCH {{BASE_URL}}/api/attendance/regularization?id={{REG_ID}}
Authorization: Bearer {{PRINCIPAL_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action":        "rejected",
  "reviewComment": "Attendance records are accurate"
}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 9 — GENERIC WORKFLOW CONFIG: Verify all types are configured
# Expected: 200, { workflow: { id, stages: [...] } } for each type
# If workflow: null → seed hasn't run yet or was skipped
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 9a. Check attendance workflow config
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/super-admin/schools/{{SCHOOL_ID}}/workflow?type=attendance
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}

###

### 9b. Check fee waiver workflow config
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/super-admin/schools/{{SCHOOL_ID}}/workflow?type=fee
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}

###

### 9c. Check parent query workflow config
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/super-admin/schools/{{SCHOOL_ID}}/workflow?type=query_parents
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}

###

### 9d. Check leave workflow config (teacher)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/super-admin/schools/{{SCHOOL_ID}}/workflow?type=leave&role=teacher
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}

###

### 9e. Check admission workflow config
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/super-admin/schools/{{SCHOOL_ID}}/workflow?type=admission
Authorization: Bearer {{SUPER_TOKEN}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 10 — LEAVE BALANCE: Verify balances loaded
# Expected: 200, { balances: [{ leaveTypeCode, daysAllowed, daysUsed, remaining }] }
# If empty → leave types or balance policy not configured
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 10. Check leave balance (teacher)
GET {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave/balance
Authorization: Bearer {{TEACHER_TOKEN}}

###

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# EDGE CASES — Run these to validate error handling
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### E1. Idempotent seed (second run — all should return "skipped")
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admin/seed-workflows
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### E2. Student role should be forbidden from seeding
# Expected: 403 Forbidden
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admin/seed-workflows
Authorization: Bearer REPLACE_WITH_STUDENT_JWT
Content-Type: application/json

{}

###

### E3. Cross-school: school_admin targeting another school → 400 (schoolId ignored)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admin/seed-workflows
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "schoolId": "different_school_uuid"
}

###

### E4. Approve admission without valid app ID → 404
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/admission/applications/nonexistent_id/action
Authorization: Bearer {{ADMIN_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action": "approve"
}

###

### E5. Submit leave without leave types configured → 404 or empty
# (Helps diagnose missing leave type master setup)
POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/leave
Authorization: Bearer {{TEACHER_TOKEN}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "leaveTypeCode": "INVALID",
  "startDate":     "2026-06-20",
  "endDate":       "2026-06-20",
  "reason":        "Test"
}

###
